post_text:
Athletic Department:
Cross Country Conditioning

Calling ALL High School Runners!! Cross Country will start conditioning for the Fall Season, Monday, July 27th, 2020 from 3:00p -5:00p. Please bring a mask, shorts, shirt, and gym shoes. A parent MUST accompany each student athlete the first day to sign the participation waiver. Physicals are also required. If a student athlete participated in sports last year, the sports physical that is already on file is acceptable. If your student has not completed a sport physical, this must be completed before participation. Sports physicals can be done at any Urgent Care Facility. The cost is typically between $15-$25. Walk ins are accepted at Urgent Care Facilities. Any further questions, please Contact Head Cross Country Coach Prey- michael.prey@hwschools.org

Mr. Ki'erre Gaut
District Wide Athletic Director
Harper Woods Public Schools
20225 Beaconsfield
Harper Woods, MI 48225

Our WXYZ-TV Channel 7 Senior Salutes: Jermarrlowe Sykes Jr. played his fourth and final football season in the fall at Harper Woods High School, but he had a big date this spring. Sykes made the MHSFCA All-Star Game.

New customers will get complimentary internet essentials service for 60 days, which is normally available to qualified low-income households for $9.95 per month, and the speeds are increasing for new and existing customers.

The speeds will be rolled out nationally over the past few days, and all new customers will be a free self-install kit that includes a cable modem and WiFi router. There is no term contract.

To sign up, applicants can simply visit www.internetessentials.com. The accessible website also includes the option to video chat with customer service agents in American Sign Language. There are also two dedicated phone numbers 1-855-846-8376 for English

post_text:
Harper Woods football players, Sophomore Christion Stokes, Junior Davion Weatherspoon (Baby D), and Junior Daveon Turner.

Christion Stokes received his 8th & 9th scholarship offers, from Michigan State University, and West Virginia University, over the last couple days! Congratulations on those football scholarship offers!

Davion Weatherspoon has 14 scholarship offers right now, his biggest being University of Michigan, University of Kentucky and Central Michigan University. Congratulations on those football scholarship offers!

Daveon Turner received his first big offer from Army University! Congratulations on that scholarship offer!

I just wanted to keep everyone in the loop of the AMAZING things still going on while we are working from home! Salute to these young men, who are continuously striving for Excellence!

Senior Curtis Jackson’s recognition, and spotlight, was aired on Channel 7 not too long ago. I’m not sure if everyone seen it, but wanted to share it with our community of support! They spotlighted his accomplishment, and his outstanding job in academics! For those who may not know, Curtis Jackson received a FULL scholarship, to attend Ferris State University, for football AND basketball! He will be playing both because he’s THAT good! Ferris State’s program is one of the top programs in the country for both football and basketball! Their basketball team won the National Championship last year!

https://www.wxyz.com/sports/wxyz-senior-salutes-harper-woods-basketball-south-lyon-soccer

Please take a second and watch his Senior Salute!

The Harper Woods School District is sponsoring an awesome event for the wonderful hardworking women of the Harper Woods community. This event is open to the first 35 woman that R.S.V.P. with the HW School District Community Relations Director. (The event is free)

Event: Painting with Passion.
Date: Sat. Feb. 1, 2020
Time: 11 am- 2 pm
Location: Harper Woods High School (Art room)
Cost: Free
If you're interested please email chaka.johnson@hwschools.org to reserve your spot today.
(Introduction to the Harper Woods Women's Club. This event is for Women only.)
This event is an opportunity for the community to enjoy food, fun and painting.
Board Member Terri Hughes will host the event. (Community Chairperson)

post_text:
In a new, collaborative initiative, The Peer-to-Peer Reading Program, several of our NHS-Dual Enrollment students spent two weeks of their time during the semester break from college classes, working with elementary students at Beacon and Tyrone to help improve reading skills.

The high school students had great things to say about this opportunity that was beneficial to them and the elementary students!

Thank you to all who supported this initiative, including but not limited to Mr. McGhee, District Office, Trish (Mrs. Colon), Mr. Watts, Principal Hughes, Principal Holley, Ms. Allemon, Ms. Doakes, Ms. Brown, and the NHS-Dual Enrollment students.

Ms. Brown from Beacon was kind enough to share pictures taken of our NHS-Dual Enrollment students working with Beacon students.

Enjoy!

You support is greatly appreciated!

post_text: In acknowledgment of Human Trafficking Prevention Month, we would like to invite the parents and their children of Harper Woods High School to join Representative Yancey in a discussion that will aim to raise awareness of Human Trafficking. We will also discuss safety precautions and prevention among not only adults but children as well. The Representative will be hosting her Human Trafficking Town Hall Friday, January 10th from 5:00 p.m-7:00 p.m. at Harper Woods High School located at 20225 Beaconsfield St, Harper Woods, MI 48225. We hope that you will help us to engage in a much needed conversation on Human Trafficking and perhaps provide information on how we can help to keep our students safe.
